  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LPI Systems Audit</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">LPI Systems Audit</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">Life and Peace Institute (LPI) &#xE4;r en internationell organisation som &#xE4;r registrerad som en stiftelse i Sverige. Sida har st&#xF6;ttat LPI:s regionala program f&#xF6;r Afrikas horn (HARP) under perioden 2017-2020 och planerar att st&#xF6;dja en ny fas av programmet fr&#xE5;n 2021 &#x2013; 2025 med 60 miljoner SEK. Dock uppstod det problem under den senaste avtalsperioden, framf&#xF6;rallt g&#xE4;llande hur LPI hanterade organisationer som f&#xE5;r vidaref&#xF6;rmedlat st&#xF6;d, samt LPI:s rutiner f&#xF6;r att uppdatera och revidera budgetar. D&#xE4;rmed togs beslutet att best&#xE4;lla en systemrevision som unders&#xF6;ker LPI:s interna kontroll och ledningssystem.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Life and Peace Institute is an international organisation registered as a foundation in Sweden. Sida has supported the LIP HARP programme during 2017 &#x2013; 2020 and is currently planning to support the new phase of the programme from 2021 &#x2013; 2025, with 60MSEK. However, during the previous agreement period, Sida in the management of this contribution faced some challenges, especially in how LPI was managing the sub-grantees and in terms of budget revision routines. Therefore, a decision was taken to commission a systems audit that focuses on the internal control and management system.</narrative>
  </description>
